<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Team Name Generator</title>
    <link href="/style.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
    <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.6.1.min.js" type="text/javascript"> </script>
    <script type='text/javascript'>
        function goToTemplate(){

            let data = {
              "leaderName": <%-JSON.stringify(leaderName) %>,
              "followerName": <%-JSON.stringify(followerName) %>,
              "condition": <%= condition %>
            };

            window.location.replace("/template/" + data.condition + "/" + data.followerName + "/en")

        }
    </script>
</head>
<body>
<h1> Team Name Generator (1/3) </h1>

<div id="main">
<!--
<div id="topThird">
<div id="instructionsLeftPad">
</div>
-->
<div id="instructions">
<p id="leaderTeamInstructions" class="text">Below are the team names that you and your team must use for the Reflective Learning Chatbot experiment. Save both of these names by either copying them down correctly or taking a screenshot of this page.

<br> <br>
You, as the manager, must use the first team name, under "<b>Leader Team Name</b>".
<br> <br>
The name under "<b>Employee Team Name</b>" is for your employees. This is the same for all employees, and it is the name that they will enter into the chatbot when it asks them for their team name. On the next page, you will find a template with this team name that you can copy and send to your employees to invite them to participate.

</div>
<!--
<div id="instructionsLeftPad">
</div>
</div>
-->
<div id="leaderDiv">
<p id="leaderTeamLabel" class="label">Leader Team Name:</p>
<p id="leaderTeamName" class="name"><%= leaderName %></p>
</div>
<div id="followerDiv">
<p id="followerTeamLabel" class="label">Employee Team Name:</p>
<p id="followerTeamName" class="name"><%= followerName %></p>
</div>
</div>
<div id="continueDiv">
<p id="continue"> Click 'Next' to proceed to the invitation template</p>
<input type="button" class="navigate-button" onclick='goToTemplate()' value="Next -->"> </input>
</div>

</body>
</html>